You're missing the **`BindingContext`** — the page doesn't know which ViewModel to bind to. Two fixes:

**1. Set the BindingContext** (e.g., in code-behind):

```csharp
public MainPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
}
```

**2. Ensure your ViewModel raises change notifications** by implementing `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or using `[ObservableProperty]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit):

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title = "Hello";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description = "World";
}
```

Without `BindingContext`, `{Binding Title}` has nothing to resolve against, so labels render blank.
